* A cursory reading would imply that nets are used to dehumanize and subdue their enemies
** Indeed, many passages support this idea - Cassandra, recently a slave, is told that she is "caught in the nets of doom - obey" when commanded by her master, and Clytaemnestra ponders "How to rig the nets of pain so high no man can overleap them" when plotting her husbands murder.
**
